---
import Layout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="🍞 Natural Breadcrumbs">
  <main>

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">🍞 Natural Breadcrumbs</h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-6">Applied category theory and programming language theory are converging on the same structures from different directions. This site maps the translations — with runnable code.</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-6" style="display:flex;gap:2em;flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">PL theory</p>
        <pre class="text-sm font-mono text-green-300" style="margin:0">assert P(x)
y = f(x)
assert R(y)
z = g(y)
assert Q(z)</pre>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">Category theory</p>
        <pre class="text-sm font-mono text-blue-300" style="margin:0">{'{P}'} f {'{R}'}    {'{R}'} g {'{Q}'}
─────────────────────
    {'{P}'} g∘f {'{Q}'}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-8">Same structure. Different notation. Each paper below gets a page that shows both — plus code you can run.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Full pipeline with feedback -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 500 200" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Forward pipeline boxes -->
        <!-- Perceive -->
        <rect x="10" y="40" width="80" height="36" rx="6" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="50" y="63" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10">Perceive</text>

        <!-- Cache -->
        <rect x="110" y="40" width="60" height="36" rx="6" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="140" y="63" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10">Cache</text>

        <!-- Filter -->
        <rect x="190" y="40" width="60" height="36" rx="6" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="220" y="63" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10">Filter</text>

        <!-- Attend -->
        <rect x="270" y="40" width="65" height="36" rx="6" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="302" y="63" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10">Attend</text>

        <!-- Remember -->
        <rect x="355" y="40" width="75" height="36" rx="6" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.1" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="392" y="63" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10">Remember</text>

        <!-- Forward wires with labels -->
        <!-- raw -->
        <line x1="90" y1="58" x2="110" y2="58" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="100" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">raw</text>

        <!-- encoded -->
        <line x1="170" y1="58" x2="190" y2="58" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="180" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">encoded</text>

        <!-- indexed -->
        <line x1="250" y1="58" x2="270" y2="58" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="260" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">indexed</text>

        <!-- ranked -->
        <line x1="335" y1="58" x2="355" y2="58" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="345" y="50" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">ranked</text>

        <!-- persisted output -->
        <line x1="430" y1="58" x2="460" y2="58" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
        <text x="460" y="50" text-anchor="end" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">persisted</text>

        <!-- Feedback loop: Remember -> down -> left -> up into Attend -->
        <!-- Down from Remember -->
        <line x1="392" y1="76" x2="392" y2="130" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
        <!-- Left along bottom -->
        <line x1="392" y1="130" x2="302" y2="130" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
        <!-- Up into Attend (second input) -->
        <line x1="302" y1="130" x2="302" y2="76" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>

        <!-- Consolidate label -->
        <text x="347" y="145" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.5">Consolidate</text>

        <!-- policy label on the feedback wire -->
        <text x="347" y="124" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="7" fill-opacity="0.45">policy</text>

        <!-- Two-input indicator on Attend: small dot where policy enters -->
        <circle cx="302" cy="76" r="2.5" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.4"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 mb-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">The papers</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">Each paper has a 🍞 page that translates its key ideas into diagrams and runnable code.</p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Paper</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Staton 2025</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Every Hoare rule is a theorem, not an axiom, in stochastic systems</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/staton-2025/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Fritz 2020</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Stochastic functions form a category with copy and discard</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/fritz-2020/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Fritz, Perrone, Rezagholi 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">"Which outputs are possible?" is a monad morphism</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/fritz-perrone-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Gaboardi 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Hoare logic with grades — track side effects through composition</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/gaboardi-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Kura 2026</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Stage N's guarantee becomes stage N+1's assumption</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/kura-2026/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Hedges, Ghani 2018</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Nash equilibrium composes the same way contracts compose</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/hedges-2018/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Capucci 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">"What is a goal but a predicate on a system?"</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/capucci-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Baez, Fritz, Leinster 2011</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Shannon entropy is the only information loss that respects composition</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/baez-fritz-2011/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Liell-Cock, Staton 2025</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Graded monads and Markov categories are the same structure</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/liell-cock-2025/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Sato, Katsumata 2023</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Distance between programs = enrichment on the category</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/sato-2023/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Spivak 2013</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Typed ports and wiring diagrams — the syntax layer for composing boxes</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/spivak-2013/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Jacobs 2014</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Weakest preconditions from fibrations over Kleisli categories</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/jacobs-2014/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Kidney, Wu 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">One monad parameterized by a semiring — probability, counting, search</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/kidney-wu-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Leinster 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Diversity IS categorical cardinality — magnitude generalizes species count</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/leinster-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Smithe 2021</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Bayesian inversions compose as lenses — forward inference, backward learning</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/smithe-2021/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Parzygnat 2020</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Bayesian inversion as dagger structure — three levels of reversibility</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/parzygnat-2020/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Di Lavore, Román, Sobocinski 2025</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Markov categories where morphisms can fail — observations, conditioning</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/di-lavore-2025/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Panangaden 2009</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Bisimulation metrics — behavioral distance between stochastic processes</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/panangaden-2009/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Cho, Jacobs 2015</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Predicates as effects, not subobjects — states/effects duality</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/cho-jacobs-2015/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Ho, Wu, Raad 2026</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Hoare logic for Bayesian programs — frame rule IS probabilistic independence</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/ho-wu-2026/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300">Chen, Vigneaux 2023</td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Shannon entropy and magnitude unified — recovers magnitude under uniform</td>
            <td><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/chen-vigneaux-2023/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">🍞</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Foundations</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">If a paper page above uses a concept you haven't seen, it probably lives in the foundations. Based on <a href="https://bartoszmilewski.com/2014/10/28/category-theory-for-programmers-the-preface/" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">Bartosz Milewski's Category Theory for Programmers</a> (<a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>), translated to runnable Python.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4"><a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/foundations/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">→ 24 chapters, same format as above</a></p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">What is this</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">An interactive companion to a <a href="https://june.kim/framework-lexicon" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">research project</a> connecting several academic communities working on the same problem with different vocabulary.</p>
    <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-1 mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
      <li>A <a href="https://github.com/kimjune01/natural-framework" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">Lean 4 proof</a> machine-checks the connections — <a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/lean/">read the proof file by file</a></li>
      <li>A <a href="https://june.kim/framework-lexicon" class="underline hover:text-gray-200">vocabulary table</a> maps terms across communities (for the researchers)</li>
      <li><strong>This site</strong> — the same ideas, in code you can run (for everyone else)</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Also: <a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/symbols/" class="underline hover:text-gray-300">symbol grid</a> · <a href="/natural-breadcrumbs/how/" class="underline hover:text-gray-300">how to use this site</a></p>

    <hr class="border-zinc-700 my-8"/>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-xs">This site is licensed <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" class="underline hover:text-gray-400">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>. Fork it, build on it, keep it open.</p>

  </main>
</Layout>
